WRITING.TITLE: Reached Global Elite - ESEA now?
WRITING.TEXT: So, i just accidentally clicked the 'back' button on my mouse after writing a long post.. Don't you hate that?.. OT: Yesterday i reached Global Elite, after fighting my way up from Double AK. I de-ranked a few times trough the process, but also i feel like I have gotten alot better because of my desire to reach the top rank. Also i should tell you that I'm not playing as serious as i did a few years back (CSS). Where i dedicated alot of my time in CS. But since GO came out i have been playing more "casually" you could say. It's still important for me to win a match, but I usually don't play very much - about 10 matches a week i think. But i experienced than once you reach the higher ranks you encounter cheaters more often, and it certainly hasn't gone better when reaching Global Elite. So what's next ? I was thinking about ESEA, and I just wanted to know what you're experiences with the system and the players? Also I wanted to know if anyone know anything about the one week premium codes that sometimes are being handed out for free ? and possible anyone would offer me one, since I do no feel like using any money on ESEA unless the community is as good as i think it to be. http://oi57.tinypic.com/11qikp1.jpg

OP here I tried faceit and i was not really that satisfied with it, often people was low skilled and also alot of people whining if a few rounds were lost.. Also do you know anything about this free week premium key that some people give away for free?

Thank you for this response. Exactly what i needed. Are people friendly on ESEA? , cause often in MM you are teamed up with idiots who blame everybody but themselves for dieing.. Do you know if there is anyway that i can get invited to try esea for a few days for free? I really do not like the idea of spending anything before i try it, and it wouldn't make sense to buy 12 months and regret afterwards.. Thank you again
OK, i just tried cevo and that was no succes.. 25-8 score on inferno, people are playing like silvers and act like 5 year olds.. Hmm.. seems like ESEA is the only way for me. Thanks

WRITING.TITLE: SCCM report returns "duplicate" machines -
WRITING.TEXT: Hi, I have created a report to get basic information from machines in a selected collection, default: SMS00001 The thing is that many of our users have more than one primary machine, which means it will return multiple rows with same computer name, because the computer has more than one primary user. See below example I get two rows * PC1234 User1 * PC1234 User2 But I want this: * PC1234 User1, User2 How would i join together the values and comma separate them? Here is the code *(To keep this simple I have only included the most relevant lines from the SQL query)* gt; SELECT distinct gt; CS.name0 as 'Computer Name', gt; UMR.UniqueUserName as 'Primary User', gt; CS.ResourceID as 'ResourceID' gt; from gt; v_GS_COMPUTER_SYSTEM CS gt; join v_FullCollectionMembership fcm on fcm.resourceid=CS.resourceid gt; right join v_UserMachineRelationship as UMR on UMR.MachineResourceID = CS.ResourceID gt; where gt; fcm.Collectionid = @Collection
